	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>All of the pets have their own places. Each pet has its strengths and weaknesses. For example, you wouldn't want to use your fire pet on a mob that casts, becuase then the mob you are fighting wouldn't hit the pet as much and therefore its damage shield would be less useful. However, the air pet that casts stun would be a great choice for that same casting mob. <br><br>It doesn't take any time for a pet to cast their spells. Pet spells go off automatically and don't interuppt the pet's melee. So you saying that the earth pet sucks becuase it wastes time casting root is wrong, it doesn't take any time for the pet to cast root.<br><br>Someone else said that chain summoning is the best way to solo as a magician. This is untrue most of the time. Chain summoning pets is not the most efficient way to level. The best way to level once you get into your teens is killing a lot of blue conning mobs. <br><br>Learn to use your pets. They are all useful, you just have to know when to use each one.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
