	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK here is what i have to say on Mages they rock and roll .:)  think about it u don't need to buy food or water, u don't hafta rely on getting a groupIE: great pets. and they r fairly easy to equip int gear.  The only downside to being a mage is the constant XP you have to deal with LOL. how do u do it????? As far as advice goes hey it's a game all i can say is have fun take a tour when u r young then kill kill kill. when u get to LVL 8 start to bear down on dieing cause the key is to die as little as possible. I know that sounds tough but it ain't!  Simply use your skills and develope a strategy that works for you i suggest pulling with your debuffer and send pet in to melee (o course that is when you get your debuffer) then DD to outdamage your pet then med rinse repeat:)You can group and it is quite important to know the tactics to grouping cause they r very different,  i have found that when in a good group u only need one good DD and good timing when to nuke that mob.  Your DS is a must and pet can tank right next to your main! but if you really want xp and money solo to 48 useing addict's gude and have fun!!!!! hey if u r ever on E'ci look me up and we will kick some &^* together<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Verax Xerav<br>E'ci Mage extraordinnaire</td></tr>
